Troubleshooting Tips
Suricata won't start:

Check interface name matches your system: ip addr show
Verify configuration syntax: sudo suricata -T -c /etc/suricata/suricata.yaml
Check permissions on log directory: sudo chmod 755 /var/log/suricata
Zeek compilation fails:

Ensure all dependencies installed: sudo apt install -y cmake make gcc g++ flex bison libpcap-dev
Check available disk space: df -h
Review compilation logs for specific errors
No alerts generated:

Verify rules are loaded: sudo suricata --dump-config | grep rule-files
Check network traffic is flowing: sudo tcpdump -i eth0 -c 10
Ensure HOME_NET matches your network range
Generate test traffic using provided commands
Python scripts fail:

Verify Python 3 installed: python3 --version
Check file permissions: chmod +x *.py
Run with sudo if accessing system logs: sudo python3 script.py
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated deploying complementary network security monitoring tools for comprehensive Layer 7 visibility. Suricata provides signature-based detection for known threats, while Zeek offers behavioral analysis and detailed protocol logging. Together, they create a powerful monitoring solution.

Key takeaways:

Layer 7 detection requires application protocol awareness
Signature-based and behavioral detection are complementary
Automation scripts enhance operational efficiency
Log correlation provides deeper security insights
Custom rules enable organization-specific detection
